Avian influenza in Japan
--------------
Follow-up report No. 1
See also: 1 Jul 2005
Information received on 28 Jul 2005 from Dr Hirofumi Kugita, Chief
Veterinary Officer, Ministry of Agriculture, Forestry and Fisheries, Tokyo:
End of previous report period: 27 Jun 2005 (see Disease Information, 18
[26], 176, dated 1 Jul 2005).
End of this report period: 15 Jul 2005.
Precise identification of agent: low pathogenic avian influenza (LPAI)
virus type H5N2.
Date of first confirmation of the event: 26 Jun 2005.
Date of start of the event: 24 Jun 2005.
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory. The affected populations showed little or
no clinical signs of the disease.
Details of outbreaks (data corrected and updated):
First administrative division (prefecture): Ibaraki
Lower administrative division: Mitsukaido city
Type of epidemiological unit: farm
Date of start of the outbreak: 24 Jun 2005
Species: avi
Number of animals in the outbreak
susceptible / cases / deaths / destroyed / slaughtered
24 504 / ... / ... / 24 504 / ...
Details of outbreaks (data corrected and updated):
First administrative division (prefecture): Ibaraki
Lower administrative division: Mitsukaido city
Type of epidemiological unit: farm*
Date of start of the outbreak: 26 Jun 2005
Species: avi
Number of animals in the outbreak
susceptible / cases / deaths / destroyed / slaughtered
123 975 / ... / ... / 123 975 / ...
Details of outbreaks (data corrected and updated):
First administrative division (prefecture): Ibaraki
Lower administrative division: Bando city
Type of epidemiological unit: farm
Date of start of the outbreak: 26 Jun 2005
Species: avi

Number of animals in the outbreak
susceptible / cases / deaths / destroyed / slaughtered
8486 / ... / ... / 8486 / ...
* 5 farms
Diagnosis:
Laboratory where diagnosis was made: National Institute of Animal Health
(national reference laboratory)
Diagnostic tests used
- agar gel precipitation test;
Date: ...
Results: positive
-PCR (1)
Date: ...
Results: ...
- pathogen isolation by egg inoculation.
Date: ...
Results: ...
Diagnostic tests used: intravenous pathogenicity index (IVPI) test
Date: 9 Jul 2005
Results: 0.0
Source of outbreak or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive.
Control measures undertaken:
- movement control on infected farms and on farms within a 5-km radius of
the infected farms;
- stamping out: all chickens on the 7 farms (including the index farm)
where diagnostic tests were positive have already been destroyed;
- disinfection of infected premises;
- on-site investigations on farms within a 5-km radius of the infected farms;
- the breeding farms where infected chickens were hatched have been
investigated, with negative results.
Vaccination prohibited: yes.
(1) PCR: polymerase chain reaction
